quran[57]{c,v,t}:
  73,20,"Verily thy Lord knoweth that thou stayest up near two- thirds of the night, Or half thereof, or a third thereof, and also a party of those who are with thee. And Allah measureth the night and the day. He knoweth that ye can compute it not, He hath relented toward you. Wherefore recite now of the Qur'an, so much as is easy. He knoweth that there will be among you some diseased, and others shall be travelling in the land seeking grace of Allah, and others shall be fighting in the way of Allah. Wherefore recite thereof so much as is easy; and establish the prayer and give the poor-rate and lend Unto Allah a goodly loan. Whatsoever good ye shall send on for your souls, ye shall find it with Allah, better and greater in reward. And ask forgiveness of Allah; verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  74,1,O thou enveloped
  74,2,"Arise, and warn"
  74,3,And thine Lord magnify
  74,4,And thine raiment purify
  74,5,And pollution shun
  74,6,And bestow not favour that thou mayest receive more
  74,7,And for the good-will of thy Lord be thou patient
  74,8,Then when the horn shall be blown
  74,9,That shall be - that Day-a day hard
  74,10,"For the infidels, not easy"
  74,11,Let Me alone with him whom I created lonely
  74,12,And for whom I appointed wealth extended
  74,13,And sons present by his side
  74,14,And for whom I smoothed everything
  74,15,And who yet coveteth that shall increase
  74,16,By no means! Verily he hath been Unto Our signs a foe
  74,17,Anon I shall afflict him with a fearful woe
  74,18,"Verily he considered, and devised"
  74,19,Perish he! How moliciously he devised
  74,20,And again perish he! How maliciously he devised
  74,21,Then looked he
  74,22,Then frowned he and scowled
  74,23,"Then turned he back, and grew stiff-necked"
  74,24,"Then he said: naught is this but magic from of old"
  74,25,Naught is this but the word of Man
  74,26,Anon shall I roast him into the Scorching Fire
  74,27,And what knoweth thou that which the Scorching Fire
  74,28,"It shall not spare, nor leave"
  74,29,Scorching the skin
  74,30,Over it are appointed nineteen
  74,31,"And We have appointed none but the angels to be wardens of the Fire. And their number we have made only a trial for those who disbelieve, so that those who are vouchsafed the Book may be convinced, and that those who believe may increase in faith, and that those who are vouchsafed the Book and the believers may not doubt, and that those in whose hearts is a disease and the infidels may say: what meaneth Allah by this description! In this wise Allah sendeth astray whomsoever He will, and guideth whomsoever He will. And none knoweth the hosts of thy Lord but He. And it is naught but an admonition Unto man"
  74,32,By no means! By the moon
  74,33,By the night when it with draweth
  74,34,By the morning when it brighteneth
  74,35,Verily it is one of the greatest woes
  74,36,A warning Unto humankind
  74,37,A warning Unto him of you who shall go forward or who chooseth to lag behind
  74,38,Every soul will be a pledge for that which it hath earned
  74,39,Save the fellows of the right
  74,40,In Gardens; they shall be asking
  74,41,Concerning the culprits
  74,42,What led you into the Scorching Fire
  74,43,They will say. 'we have not been of those who prayed
  74,44,And we have not been feeding the poor
  74,45,And we have been wading with the waders
  74,46,And we have been belying the Day of Requital
  74,47,until there came to us the certainty
  74,48,Then there will not Profit them intercision of the interceders
  74,49,"What aileth them, therefore, that they are from the Admonition turning away"
  74,50,As though they were asses startled
  74,51,Fleeing away from a lion
  74,52,"Aye! every one of them desireth that: he should be vouchsafed scrolls expanded"
  74,53,"By no means! Aye, they fear not the Hereafter"
  74,54,By no means! Verily this Qur'an is an Admonition
  74,55,So whosoever willeth may heed it
  74,56,And they shall not heed unless Allah Willeth. He is the Lord of piety. and the Lord of forgiveness